title: First Taekwondo Competition: Challenging Club wins title
text:
First Taekwondo Competition: Challenging Club wins title October 26, 2015 
Challenging Club, coached by Mohammed al Harthy, won a total of 21 medals, including six gold, six silver and nine bronze, to claim the First Taekwondo Competition for the Korean Ambassador's Trophy at the Sultan Qaboos Sports Complex recently. 
H E Daesik Kim, South Korea's ambassador to Oman and Col Abdulmalik. 
Al Mazroui, the chairman of the Oman Taekwondo Committee, gave away the awards. The event, jointly organised by the Ministry of Sports Affairs and the South Korean Embassy in Oman, saw the participation of leading taekwondo clubs in the sultanate. Similar content
